irst endocrine cells to differentiate","Delta cells differentiate before alpha cells","PP cells differentiate before delta cells"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe endocrine pancreas develops from two endodermal buds (dorsal and ventral) that emerge from the primitive foregut. The buds then fuse to form the pancreas.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlpha cells\u003C/strong\u003E are the first endocrine cells to differentiate in pancreatic development, followed by \u003Cstrong\u003Ebeta cells\u003C/strong\u003E. The sequence of endocrine cell differentiation is: glucagon-producing \u003Cstrong\u003Ealpha cells\u003C/strong\u003E \u2192 insulin-producing beta cells \u2192 somatostatin-producing \u003Cstrong\u003Edelta cells\u003C/strong\u003E \u2192 \u003Cstrong\u003EPP cells\u003C/strong\u003E that produce pancreatic polypeptide.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis developmental sequence ensures proper establishment of the complex regulatory networks within the pancreatic islets.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Alpha cells are the first endocrine cells to differentiate in pancreatic development","The endocrine pancreas develops from fusion of dorsal and ventral pancreatic buds from the primitive foregut","The sequence of pancreatic endocrine cell differentiation is: alpha cells \u2192 beta cells \u2192 delta cells \u2192 PP cells"],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015.","Meier JJ, K\u00f6hler CU, Alkhatib B, Sergi C, Junker T, Klein HH, Schmidt WE, Fritsch H. Beta-cell development and turnover during prenatal life in humans. Eur J Endocrinol. 2010 Mar;162(3):559-68.","Saleh M, Gittes GK, Prasadan K. Alpha-to-beta cell trans-differentiation for treatment of diabetes. Biochem Soc Trans. 2021;49(6):2539-2548. doi:10.1042/BST20210244"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58323"}},"question":{"data":{"ty